						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">emu_enthusiast wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So the interesting thing to me is now, can the same thing be done in the ROM itself rather than in the emulator?</div>
<br />
<br />No. Getting a NROM game to work with an automatic patcher may work. But ultimately you can't automate a process to get the vast majority of NES games to run on SNES. The reason being mappers. That's why all the AS NES hacks are of NROM games. 
<br />
<br />You could probably adapter any NES game to SNES if you do it by hand though. If you have both the skills and alot of time.</div>

